<title>USA: Perpetual Bank revised Q2 EPS $0.28.</title>
<headline>Perpetual Bank revised Q2 EPS $0.28.</headline>
<dateline>ANDERSON, S.C. 1997-06-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>(in thousands, except per share amounts)</p>
<p>					    Six Months	 Quarter</p>
<p>					 Ended March 31  Ended March 31</p>
<p> Operating Data:		     1997    1996    1997    1996</p>
<p> Interest income		  $ 8,589 $ 7,276 $ 4,407 $ 3,737</p>
<p> Interest expense		   4,294   3,695   2,293   1,921</p>
<p> Provision for loan losses	  175     125     145	94</p>
<p>Net interest income after</p>
<p>  provision for loan losses     4,120   3,456   1,969   1,722</p>
<p> Other income			 1,225     920     714     464</p>
<p>General and administrative</p>
<p>  expenses			    3,849   3,012   2,051   1,564</p>
<p>Income before income tax</p>
<p>  provision			   1,496   1,364     632     622</p>
<p> Provision for income taxes	 509     464     215     212</p>
<p> Net income			     987     900     417     410</p>
<p> Net income per share		0.66    0.60    0.28    0.27</p>
<p> Return on assets		   0.88%   0.98%   0.71%   0.91%</p>
<p> Return on equity		   6.65%   9.47%   5.63%   8.81%</p>
<p> Dividends per share		 0.60    0.60    0.30    0.30</p>
<p>Weighted average shares</p>
<p>  outstanding			 1,505   1,505   1,505   1,505</p>
<p>NOTES: The company said the earnings revision follows an error in the calculation of interest income on loans previously sold in the secondary market.</p>
<p>It said it had previously reported second quarter earnings of $604,000, or $0.40 a share.</p>
<p>Full co name is Perpetual Bank, A Federal Savings Bank.</p>
